36:36.000 --> 36:38.200
- Amy Juergens?
- Amy Juergens.

36:39.300 --> 36:40.200
Huh.

36:41.400 --> 36:42.200
Yikes.

36:46.300 --> 36:47.400
Don't run away from me.

36:47.400 --> 36:49.100
I'll just run after you, both of you.

36:49.300 --> 36:50.700
Who's running?

36:51.500 --> 36:54.500
I can't believe I was so stupid
to think that ?? just kissed.

36:55.500 --> 36:56.700
Me, neither.

36:56.700 --> 36:59.500
He told me, he told me that's all
that was going on, just kissing.

36:59.500 --> 37:01.900
Mm, please. This is so boring.

37:01.900 --> 37:05.000
Is it? It's boring to you when
you ruin somebody else's life?

37:05.000 --> 37:06.800
Did someone here ruin your life?

37:06.800 --> 37:09.300
Yeah, he did. Jack did.

37:09.500 --> 37:12.800
He was my boyfriend, my first
boyfriend, and he cheated on me

37:12.800 --> 37:15.600
and lied to me, and I in turn
had to lie to my parents,

37:15.600 --> 37:17.300
and now I don't know if they're
ever gonna trust me again

37:17.300 --> 37:19.500
or if I'm ever gonna trust
another guy ever again.

37:19.500 --> 37:21.000
And yet you're friends with Ricky.

37:21.000 --> 37:21.800
You trust him?

37:21.800 --> 37:23.500
- At least he's honest.
- Is he?

37:23.800 --> 37:26.200
Then ask him if he's the
father of Amy Juergens' baby.

37:32.100 --> 37:33.100
Have you seen Amy?

37:33.800 --> 37:36.200
Juergens. Amy Juergens,
the French horn player.

37:36.200 --> 37:38.000
She didn't show up for practice.

37:41.800 --> 37:43.400
So Amy's really having a baby?

37:43.400 --> 37:44.100
Yeah.

37:44.300 --> 37:45.900
So run along and tell mommy.

37:46.200 --> 37:47.300
You win, Grace.

37:47.300 --> 37:49.100
You're the good girl, and Amy isn't.

37:49.300 --> 37:50.200
Although when you tell your parents,

37:50.200 --> 37:52.700
I doubt you'll be able to
see Ricky anymore, huh?

37:52.900 --> 37:56.900
No, it has to be Ben's. Ricky
would never make a mistake like that.

37:57.600 --> 37:58.500
And I would know.

38:00.100 --> 38:02.000
I guess you would know
about her, too, huh?

38:02.500 --> 38:05.100
- You should be ashamed of yourself.
- Oh, shut up, Grace.

38:05.400 --> 38:06.700
I'm tired of being ashamed of myself.

38:06.700 --> 38:09.700
I've been ashamed of myself my
whole life, so just shut up.

38:11.000 --> 38:12.300
?? Is that too honest for you?

38:13.100 --> 38:14.400
Thought you liked honesty.

38:15.200 --> 38:16.600
So let me tell you something else.

38:17.300 --> 38:20.000
I only went out with you
'cause my stepdad asked me to.

38:21.500 --> 38:22.100
He wanted to make sure

38:22.100 --> 38:24.900
you and your perfect little
family were happy at church.

38:26.700 --> 38:27.900
How's that for honesty?

38:41.700 --> 38:42.600
Yeah.

38:45.700 --> 38:47.600
Ah, well, look who's here,

38:47.800 --> 38:49.900
just minutes before my next appointment.

38:50.500 --> 38:51.700
You should've called, Ricky.

38:52.000 --> 38:55.000
I wanna talk to you.
But what's goin' on?

38:55.500 --> 38:58.300
- I'll come back.
- Good, good. Yeah, you come back.

38:58.600 --> 39:01.700
But before you go, what's goin' on?

39:03.700 --> 39:04.800
I, um...

39:06.500 --> 39:08.900
I heard this rumor that
I got a girl pregnant.

39:11.100 --> 39:15.100
Ah. Um, is there any truth to that rumor?

39:16.100 --> 39:17.000
Maybe.

39:19.300 --> 39:20.100
Sit down.

39:22.700 --> 39:24.600
I'll cancel the next appointment.

39:39.000 --> 39:39.700
Amy.

39:43.200 --> 39:44.000
Just...

39:44.000 --> 39:45.300
Staring at the moon?

39:45.900 --> 39:46.800
Kind of.

39:46.800 --> 39:48.600
I used to do that a lot when I was little,

39:49.600 --> 39:50.900
just stare at the moon.

39:52.500 --> 39:54.600
Seemed like the perfect
place to run away to,

39:54.600 --> 39:58.100
place where I could eat freeze-
dried ice cream and drink Tang.

39:59.000 --> 40:00.300
Bounce around all day.

40:01.200 --> 40:02.900
You really thought about
running away to the moon?

40:02.900 --> 40:03.800
Oh, yeah.

40:05.200 --> 40:08.400
There was no place on earth far enough
away from whatever was bothering me.

40:11.700 --> 40:13.300
You thinking about running
away to the moon?

40:13.900 --> 40:15.100
I wasn't, but...

40:16.400 --> 40:18.200
you made it sound like so much fun.

40:25.400 --> 40:26.300
Good night, Mom.

40:26.800 --> 40:27.900
I love you, Amy,

40:28.600 --> 40:30.300
no matter what happens.

40:30.800 --> 40:33.400
N-No matter w-w-w-what happens?

40:33.400 --> 40:34.400
With your father.

40:36.000 --> 40:38.400
I want you to remember that I love you

40:39.000 --> 40:40.300
and he loves you, too,

40:41.600 --> 40:42.400
OK?

40:43.200 --> 40:43.900
Good night.

41:12.200 --> 41:13.400
Hi, Amy Juergens.

41:14.100 --> 41:15.500
Ben Boykewich here.

41:16.300 --> 41:17.000
Huh,

41:17.500 --> 41:19.100
remember the first time I called you?

41:19.700 --> 41:21.200
Seems like a million years ago.

41:22.800 --> 41:26.500
But when we're married and we
spend like 75 years together,

41:26.700 --> 41:28.000
it'll seem like yesterday.

41:29.600 --> 41:30.700
OK. Well... 

41:32.700 --> 41:35.100
Come on, marry me.

41:36.400 --> 41:38.700
People used to get married
when they were 14, didn't they?

41:39.300 --> 41:40.000
I don't know,

41:40.800 --> 41:43.600
kings and queens and
pharaohs or something.

41:44.300 --> 41:46.900
Mayans. I don't know.

41:49.000 --> 41:51.000
I just know I love you

41:52.600 --> 41:55.300
and the offer of marriage
is good for a lifetime.

41:56.500 --> 41:57.900
So you just let me know when and where,

41:57.900 --> 42:00.100
